      • relativizeURI

        public static java.net.URI relativizeURI(java.net.URI sourceURI,
                                         java.net.URI targetURI,
                                         boolean msCompatible)
        Fully relativize the source part URI against the target part URI.(将源部分URI与目标部分URI完全相对化。)
        Parameters:
        sourceURI - The source part URI.(sourceURI -源部分URI。)
        targetURI - The target part URI.(targetURI -目标部分URI。)
        msCompatible - if true then remove leading slash from the relativized URI. This flag violates [M1.4]: A part name shall start with a forward slash ('/') character, but allows generating URIs compatible with MS Office and OpenOffice.(msCompatible -如果为真，则从相对化的URI中删除前斜线。此标志违反了[M1.4]：部件名称应以正斜线（'/'）字符开头，但允许生成与MS Office和OpenOffice兼容的uri。)
        Returns:
        A fully relativize part name URI ('word/media/image1.gif', '/word/document.xml' => 'media/image1.gif') else null.(完全相对化部件名称URI（' word/media/image1.gif '，'/word/document.html '=>'）否则为空。)

      • isValidPartName

        public static boolean isValidPartName(java.net.URI partUri)
        Validate a part URI by returning a boolean. ([M1.1],[M1.3],[M1.4],[M1.5],[M1.6]) (OPC Specifications 8.1.1 Part names) : Part Name Syntax The part name grammar is defined as follows: part_name = 1*( "/" segment ) segment = 1*( pchar ) (pchar is defined in RFC 3986)(通过返回布尔值来初始化部分URI。（[M1.1]、[M1.3]、[M1.4]、[M1.5]、[M1.6]）（IPC规范8.1.1零件名称）：零件名称语法定义如下：零件名称= 1*（“/”segment）segment = 1 *（pchar）（pchar在RFC 3986中定义）)
        Parameters:
        partUri - The URI to validate.(PartUri -要验证的URL。)
        Returns:
        true if the URI is valid to the OPC Specifications, else false(如果该URL对OPC规范有效，则为真，否则为假)
        See Also:
        createPartName(URI)

      • toURI

        public static java.net.URI toURI(java.lang.String value)
                          throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Convert a string to URI If part name is not a valid URI, it is resolved as follows:

        1. Percent-encode each open bracket ([) and close bracket (]). 2. Percent-encode each percent (%) character that is not followed by a hexadecimal notation of an octet value. 3. Un-percent-encode each percent-encoded unreserved character. 4. Un-percent-encode each forward slash (/) and back slash (\). 5. Convert all back slashes to forward slashes. 6. If present in a segment containing non-dot (?.?) characters, remove trailing dot (?.?) characters from each segment. 7. Replace each occurrence of multiple consecutive forward slashes (/) with a single forward slash. 8. If a single trailing forward slash (/) is present, remove that trailing forward slash. 9. Remove complete segments that consist of three or more dots. 10. Resolve the relative reference against the base URI of the part holding the Unicode string, as it is defined in ?5.2 of RFC 3986. The path component of the resulting absolute URI is the part name.

        (将字符串转换为URL如果部件名称不是有效的URL，则解析如下：1.对每个开括号（[）和闭括号（]）进行大写编码。2.对后面没有八位字节值十六进制表示法的每个百分比（%）字符进行字节编码。3.对每个字节编码的未保留字符进行非百分比编码。4.对每个正斜线（/）和反斜线（\）进行非百分比编码。5.将所有后斜线转换为前斜线。6.如果出现在包含非点（？.？）的段中字符，删除尾随点（？.？）每个片段中的字符。7.用单个正斜线替换每次出现的多个连续正斜线（/）。8.如果存在单个尾随正斜线（/），请删除该尾随正斜线。9.删除由三个或更多点组成的完整片段。10.解决相对于保存Unicode字符串的部分的基URL的相对引用，正如在？中定义的那样5.2的RFC 3986。生成的绝对URI的路径组件是部件名称。)
        Parameters:
        value - the string to be parsed into a URI(值-要解析为URI的字符串)
        Returns:
        the resolved part name that should be OK to construct a URI TODO YK: for now this method does only (5). Finish the rest.(已解析的部件名称应该可以构建一个URI TODO YN：目前该方法仅执行（5）。完成剩下的。)
        Throws:
        java.net.URISyntaxException(java.net.URISyntaxException)

      • encode

        public static java.lang.String encode(java.lang.String s)
        percent-encode white spaces and characters above 0x80.

        Examples:

           'Apache POI' --> 'Apache%20POI'
   'ApacheАPOI' --> 'Apache%04%10POI'
        (对0x 80以上的空白和字符进行大写编码。例子： “Apache LTD”-->“Apache %20 LTD” ' Apache '-->' Apache %04%10LTD ')
        Parameters:
        s - the string to encode(s -要编码的字符串)
        Returns:
        the encoded string(编码的字符串)
